Users are welcome to contribute to Gentoo, even those who are new! User contributions make help Gentoo run smoothly; there is always room for improvement!

There are ''many'' different topics for you to explore; thus, a question for you: ''What are you interested in?''

Those who are interested in becoming a Gentoo developer can start contributing in one of the areas listed below. Developers will see your efforts standing out among other community members (it's good to have a track record of ways you've contributed).

== Support the community ==

You can help users in various support mediums:

* [https://forums.gentoo.org/search.php?search_id=unanswered Answer unanswered questions], share how you solved a problem or discuss on the [https://forums.gentoo.org/ Gentoo Forums].
* [https://www.gentoo.org/get-involved/irc-channels/ Join our IRC channels] if you prefer direct communication, the main IRC channel for users is {{IRC|gentoo}}.
* [https://www.gentoo.org/get-involved/mailing-lists/ Subscribe at our mailing lists], the main mailing list for users is [https://archives.gentoo.org/gentoo-user/ gentoo-user].

== Document useful information ==

[https://wiki.gentoo.org Gentoo Wiki] gathers information about Gentoo and the hardware and software that it runs; you are welcome to add and edit articles:

* [[Help:Starting_a_new_page|Start a new wiki article]] to document a new subject, knowledge or package.
* [[Help:Editing_pages|Improve existing documentation]] by clicking '''Edit''' at the top right of an article.
* [[Help:Translating#For_Anyone:_Becoming_a_translator|Translate documentation]] for foreign readers.

Those who'd like to get involved in documentation should take a look at the [[Gentoo Wiki:Contributor's Guide|Contributor's Guide]] and the [[Gentoo Wiki:Guidelines|Wiki Guidelines]].

== Report and resolve bugs ==

[https://bugs.gentoo.org Gentoo Bugzilla] is where we track bugs of Gentoo and its packages; you are welcome to report, confirm and resolve bugs:

* [[Bugzilla/Bug_report_guide|Report a bug]] at our [https://bugs.gentoo.org Gentoo Bugzilla] whenever you come across an error, flaw, failure or fault; [[Bugzilla/Guide|Bugzilla guide]] provides more in-depth information when you need to provide more details.
* [https://bugs.gentoo.org/buglist.cgi?chfield=%5BBug%20creation%5D&chfieldfrom=-1D&chfieldto=Now&list_id=2122804&order=bugs.bug_id&query_format=advanced Confirm open bugs] by reproducing them, this helps consolidate the cause as well as highlight severe bugs.
* [https://sites.google.com/site/yacoset/Home/how-to-fix-bugs-step-by-step Offer solutions for open bugs]; patches, ebuilds and links to upstream (or other distribution) bug reports are welcome.
* [[Bugday|Participate in our monthly Bugday]], squashing bugs together with Gentoo Developers.

== Maintain and test packages ==

The Gentoo tree is the heart of Gentoo; it is important to keep it alive and kicking, that's why contributions to it are very valuable.

If you want to do occasional commits to either the Gentoo tree or an overlay, or become a Gentoo Developer; [[Basic_guide_to_write_Gentoo_Ebuilds|writing ebuilds]] is what makes building and installing using a package manager possible on a Gentoo system.

After the first steps, you can [https://devmanual.gentoo.org/ learn more in our Development Guide].

When you want to add a new package, update an existing one or find new packages to contribute to; these resources are for you:

* [[Bugzilla/Guide|Report version bumps]] for existing packages at our [https://bugs.gentoo.org Gentoo Bugzilla].
* [[Submitting_ebuilds|Submit a new package]] for the Gentoo tree; when you want to maintain that new package, contact the [[Project:Proxy_Maintainers|proxy maintainers]].
* [[Project:Proxy_Maintainers|Proxy-maintain]] some of our [https://qa-reports.gentoo.org/output/maintainer-needed.html orphaned packages].
* [[Project:X86/Arch_Testers_FAQ|Become an arch tester]]; for instance, check out the arch teams [[Project:X86_Arch_Testers|x86]] and [[Project:AMD64|amd64]].
* [https://www.gentoo.org/get-involved/become-developer/ Become a Gentoo Developer] and join one or more of the many [[Project:Gentoo/Staffing_Needs|projects]].
* [[Gentoo Github]] - Helping the Gentoo project and considering sending a [https://github.com/gentoo/gentoo/pulls Pull Request via GitHub]

